		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/10/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 09:43:55</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=469"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=469')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=38092&amp;TOPIC_ID=4802&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Temple+of+Droga+help+needed+please%21%21&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         That place can be rough, as there are usually a butt-load of healers there, a higher percentage that tends to be present on a chief run. The secret tunnel that is mentioned is the safest set-up point around there, but there is one wanderer that will agro. </P><P>The pathing there is horrific, and will add much misery to you at times. The worst is probably the wide ramp just down from the the secret tunnel. If you cast on a gobbie on the main floor, and you are standing back from the ramp, the goblin does not come up the ramp, rather paths around the back loop and comes at you that way. However, if you stand on the ramp and cast, the gobbie will come straight at you.</P><P>The big thing to watch is pet agro (even with the new changes). You should be able to single pull easily at 51, so if you are solo, and get a runner, no biggie, it will not bring adds back. If you are solo, you should be able to use fear safely. However, if you are fighting with a pet, and you get a runner, your pet is on the runner's hate list, and because your pet is a lower level, agros the gobbies the runner runs past. The thing that often happens here is you are fighting with a pet, you move slightly, and the pathing of the gobbie, instead of taking a straight line at you, goes into some wierd circlular path, which often puts it in agro range of other gobbies (due to your pet's level). Boom, you got company.</P><P>If you are using a pet, you need to have air tight pet and runner control. If not, it becomes an excercise in frustration down there. </P><P>Cheers,<BR>Ancagalon the Black<BR>Warlock - Terris Thule</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
