        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote> Isn't that where Stone of Morid drops? Any tips on that? I still have to get one =(<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Yes, it drops off goblin fanatics which are rare spawns at any of the points around the pool room.  It used to be fairly common, but was made much rarer when it was made usable by additional races.  The tome of the eternal used to be rare, now it is much more common.</P><P>This area gets easy to do once you hit 49.  Like people said summon a pet in the safe hall (1 roamer).  Once the roamer is dead, pull the statics from the room at the top of the ramp (thru the false wall).  As long as you stay in the safe hall or the room at the top of the ramp, it's safe and advisable to fear/kite all of the healers (legates, adepts).</P><P>The mosstroopers and fanatics are SKs.  They'll HT you for around 350 unresistable, so don't pull them if you're low on health.</P><P>Spells I use when doing this camp are :</P><P>Arch Shielding<BR>Lich<BR>Dooming Darkness<BR>Invoke Fear<BR>Bond of Death<BR>49 Pet with Haste<BR>Screaming Terror<BR>Bond of Death<BR>Feign Death</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
